{"title_page": "SS United Group Oil & Gas Company", "text_new": "{{Other uses|SS United (disambiguation)}}\n'''SS United Group Oil & Gas Company Limited''' ('''SUG''') is a company, claiming to be an [[oil]] [[trading company]] supplying [[petroleum]] products and \"advanced energy technologies\" in [[China]], [[Russia]], [[Japan]], [[Thailand]] and [[Malaysia]]. The company described itself as a [[Hong Kong]]-based [[joint venture]] between SS United Oil & Gas Company  Ltd. and Saha Regal Best Company Ltd., a Thai [[investment company]] involved in infrastructure projects in [[Thailand]] and [[Indochina]].\n\n==Formula One sponsor==\n[[Image:Anthony Davidson 2007 Bahrain (crop).jpg|thumb|The [[Super Aguri SA07]] with ''SS United'' logo]]\nDirectly before the [[2007 Australian Grand Prix]] it was announced that the company was title [[sponsor (commercial)|sponsor]] of the [[Super Aguri F1|Super Aguri]] [[Formula One]] team. The company name ''SS United'' appeared on the rear wing of the cars.<ref>{{Cite web| title = SUPER AGURI F1 TEAM WELCOMES SS UNITED GROUP AS SPONSOR | publisher = Super Aguri F1 official website | date = 2007-03-16 | url = http://www.saf1.co.jp/en/topics/2007/nws_070316_1.html | accessdate =2007-08-16}}</ref>\n\nSS United defaulted on sponsorship payments<ref>{{Cite web| title = Campos confirms Super Aguri talks | publisher = GPUpdate.net | date = 2007-08-16 | url = http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/163225/campos-confirms-super-aguri-talks/ | accessdate =2011-02-01}}</ref> which caused cashflow problems for Super Aguri and forced them to seek alternative sponsors.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Super Aguri searching for investors | publisher = GPUpdate.net | date = 2007-08-14 | url = http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/163097/super-aguri-searching-for-investors/ | accessdate =2011-02-01}}</ref> In the same month the SS United website was closed.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070427045403/http://www.ssunited-group.com/ SS United official website] on 2007 April from [https://archive.org/ Internet Archive].</ref>\n\nOn 6 May 2008, the Super Aguri F1 Team withdrew from the Formula One Championship, citing SS United's breach of contract as a major cause for the team's demise.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Energy in Hong Kong]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ss United Group Oil and Gas Company}}\n[[Category:Oil and gas companies of Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of establishment missing]]\n\n\n{{Petroleum-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|SS United (disambiguation)}}\n'''SS United Group Oil & Gas Company Limited''' ('''SUG''') is a company, claiming to be an [[oil]] [[trading company]] supplying [[petroleum]] products and \"advanced energy technologies\" in [[China]], [[Russia]], [[Japan]], [[Thailand]] and [[Malaysia]]. The company described itself as a [[Hong Kong]]-based [[joint venture]] between SS United Oil & Gas Company  Ltd. and Saha Regal Best Company Ltd., a Thai [[investment company]] involved in infrastructure projects in [[Thailand]] and [[Indochina]].\n\n==Formula One sponsor==\n[[Image:Anthony Davidson 2007 Bahrain (crop).jpg|thumb|The [[Super Aguri SA07]] with ''SS United'' logo]]\nDirectly before the [[2007 Australian Grand Prix]] it was announced that the company was title [[sponsor (commercial)|sponsor]] of the [[Super Aguri F1|Super Aguri]] [[Formula One]] team. The company name ''SS United'' appeared on the rear wing of the cars.<ref>{{Cite web| title = SUPER AGURI F1 TEAM WELCOMES SS UNITED GROUP AS SPONSOR | publisher = Super Aguri F1 official website | date = 2007-03-16 | url = http://www.saf1.co.jp/en/topics/2007/nws_070316_1.html | accessdate =2007-08-16}}</ref>\n\nSS United defaulted on sponsorship payments<ref>{{Cite web| title = Campos confirms Super Aguri talks | publisher = GPUpdate.net | date = 2007-08-16 | url = http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/163225/campos-confirms-super-aguri-talks/ | accessdate =2011-02-01}}</ref> which caused cashflow problems for Super Aguri and forced them to seek alternative sponsors.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Super Aguri searching for investors | publisher = GPUpdate.net | date = 2007-08-14 | url = http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/163097/super-aguri-searching-for-investors/ | accessdate =2011-02-01}}</ref> In the same month the SS United website was closed.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070427045403/http://www.ssunited-group.com/ SS United official website] on 2007 April from [https://archive.org/ Internet Archive].</ref>\n\nOn 6 May 2008, the Super Aguri F1 Team withdrew from the Formula One Championship, citing SS United's breach of contract as a major cause for the team's demise.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Energy in Hong Kong]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ss United Group Oil and Gas Company}}\n[[Category:Oil and gas companies of Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of establishment missing]]\n\n\n{{Petroleum-company-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SS_United_Group_Oil_%26_Gas_Company"}
